	Abstract Class 
		A class with abstract (unimplemented) methods and/or concrete methods.
		Abstract methods can have public, protected, or default access.
		When classes are closely related or you need common behavior and state. 
		Can Have constructors.
		public, protected, private access modifier
		
	Interface
		A collection of abstract methods (by default) that define a contract. 
		A class that implements an interface must provide implementations for its methods.
		Does not have constructors.
		public access modifier.
	